data.description: Executive Level home with major upgrades.  This wonderful home of 4 bedrooms and 2 ½ baths, definitely shows pride in ownership.  Wait until the large rose bushes come into bloom.  You are met at the home with “Old Glory” flying on a telescoping flagpole and a private entrance controlled by an electronic gate with an asphalt driveway, recently refinished. Some of the many upgrades include, new paint, refinished hardwood floors, metal slide outs in the kitchen cabinets, newer Kitchen Aide appliances, enclosed jacuzzi room.  The master bath is one of luxury with a shower with body massage jets.   The Master Closet is huge, more than enough room, and the Master BR is huge also, as we had room for my wife's home office and we still had room to spare.  I used the 4th BR as my home office.  The home is wired for sound with speakers in the ceiling in the living room, dining room, spa room, (the jacuzzi in the spa room will convey), outside patio, and the master bedroom.  The pressure tank from the well has been replaced, the A/C compressor has been replaced with a new one, and the home is serviced by a tankless water heater, so you have unlimited hot water.  The septic tank has been serviced and cleaned out.  The home is serviced by a water softener, filtering all water from the well.  This 5 +/- acres of land is completely fenced with an electronic gate, and an asphalt driveway.  There is heavy gauge farm fencing on the inside of the vinyl fencing, to keep your pets in and restrict other animals from entering.    There are cattle gates / drive through gates on the back end of both sides of the property if needed.  All trees are on a drip line, fed by the well.  Out back is an extremely large shop that matches the house, to house all of your tools, projects, ATV’s / UTV/s / tractors / equipment, etc., measuring 40' deep and 36' wide on inside dimensions / 48' in depth and 40' outside dimensions.   There are three mobile work benches in the shop that will convey.  This shop allows for the parking of 6-8 additional vehicles, inside the containers for UTVs / ATV's / Tractors / Trucks / vehicles in the open area.  The television mounted above the fireplace and stereo may convey if desired.  Being located at the end of the cul de sac, there is no traffic, so if peaceful luxury is what you are looking for, this is the home for you.  NOTE:  With the opening of the two mines in the local area of Yerington and surround areas, this home will only increase in value.  The shortage of construction material and exceptionally high costs of construction drive up the costs of lower quality home with just the basics.   The nicer upgrades are now out of the reach of many, as well as the time to get the materials and schedule labor, if you can find them.  This home is complete...one needs to only move in and add your personal touches to make this executive home all yours!!!! UPDATE:  We have since, refinished the hardwood floors in the Kitchen / Entrance / Breakfast Room.  We have also refinished ALL of the cabinets in the Master Bath / Kitchen / and Laundry Room...we have re calked and resealed the granite counters in the kitchen and the counter-top in the laundry room, as well as polished the granite to a very high gloss.  This home is now better than new with all the upgrades and care of this home.  Our next project on the upgrades, as the temperatures improve, is to begin resurfacing the front porch and the back patio, seal the cement, and coat it with a slate grey epoxy that will greatly enhance the home.  Fertilizer has been put down and the yard is still lush and green.   I am not sure you will find one as well taken care of and upgraded as this one, come by and see it, you just may be impressed.   NOTE:  Have completed the process of resurfacing and sealing the asphalt driveway in front of the house, leading to a 3-car attached garage.     If you desire to see this home, with no pressure, please let us know...you are more than welcome.
data.whatILove: Truly Peaceful, No streetlights...nothing but stars as far as one can see.  No traffic...eagles, hawks, owls, coyotes, deer, and all wildlife runs free.   The additional parking in the barn / shop protects all your vehicles from the harsh elements.
